      • getFalsepositives

        public int getFalsepositives(java.util.LinkedList<javafx.util.Pair<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Integer>> gTsceneCuts,
                             java.util.LinkedList<java.lang.Boolean> cutsObtained)
        Description copied from interface: PrecisionAnalyzer
        This function returns the number of false positives based on gTsceneCuts and cutsObtained. The false positives are those frames considered as cuts based on the automatic video segmentation but also NOT considered as cuts by the ground truth file submmited.
        Specified by:
        getFalsepositives in interface PrecisionAnalyzer
        Parameters:
        gTsceneCuts - Collection of tuples of the range of frames of the cuts. Being that the beginning of a scene cut and the end of the scene cut. All the frames located in this range should be considered as frames.
        cutsObtained - Plain collection of boolean values that represent the existence of a cut between two frames. If the ith value of this collection is true, this would represent a cut between the ith cut and the i+1th cut.
        Returns:
        The number of false positives according to the ground truth file submitted and the cuts obtained from the automatic video segmentation.
